    "parts of sentences are just labeled, e.g., P or I, whereas our approach considers PICO elements to be nested structures, i.e.",
    "templates with slots that have to be filled with some portion of text.",
    "Examples for this simplified view on PICO elements are listed in the following:Schmidt et al. [54] treat the PICO recognition task as a sentence classification/question answering task and thus, in contrast to the approach presented in this paper, do not work on the level of whole documents/abstracts or PICO elements which span multiple sentences.",
    "Therefore, Schmidt et al. [54] do not benefit from contextualized representations utilizing the whole abstract as a context.",
